frameDefinitions: A Traveller leaves from or dismounts a Vehicle.
An Agent causes a Useful_location to become accessible (or non-accessible) to a Theme to a certain Degree.
A Guest stays for a time at a Location, which is not his or her permanent residence, for some Duration.
This frame consists of LUs which denote a Theme ceasing motion.
A Student enrolls and then remains at an Institution for the purposes of education within a Subject.
Geography as defined by its use.
frameExamples: They've <t>blockaded</t> the entrance -- no one can get in or out.
I usually <t>stay</t> with my aunt at her summer house when I go to Seville.
Peter <t>stopped</t> immediately and span to see Aeryn frozen where she stood.
He spent ten years <t>studying</t> physics at the lycee before he flunked out.
You must land in the next <t><fex name='Locale'>airfield</fex></t>, as this one is currently having difficulties.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Traveller</fen> is the entity which disembarks from the <fen>Vehicle</fen>.
The <fen>Vehicle</fen> is the means of conveyance that the <fen>Traveller</fen> disembarks from.
When the disembarking of the <fen>Vehicle</fen> takes place.
The location in which the <fen>Traveller</fen> disembarks from the <fen>Vehicle</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> blocks access to the <fen>Useful_location</fen>.
The <fen>Useful_location</fen> is the place the <fen>Theme</fen> is headed towards and the <fen>Agent</fen> has changed the accessibility of.

The <fen>Agent</fen> may regulate access to the <fen>Useful_location</fen> by regulating access to a <fen>Portal</fen>, including a part of the portal that could block potential <fen>Theme</fen>s, such as doors or gates.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> changes the accessibility of the <fen>Useful_location</fen>.
The general <fen>Place</fen> where the blocking or allowing of access occurs.
The <fen>Guest</fen> remains for a relatively short period of time in the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Location</fen> where the <fen>Guest</fen> spends a short amount of time.
The length of time that the <fen>Guest</fen> remains at the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Host</fen> is living at the <fen>Location</fen> on a permanent basis, and is allowing the <fen>Guest</fen> to stay there.
The time at which the temporary stay takes place.
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates the larger physical setting of the temporary stay.
This role identifies <fen>Theme</fen> whose motion ceases.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Theme</fen> stops.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Theme</fen>'s motion stops.
One who instructs a <fen>Student</fen> in some area of knowledge or skill.
One who receives instruction from a <fen>Teacher</fen> or <fen>Institution</fen>.
An educational establishment, such as a school or college.
The area of knowledge or skill which is taught  to a <fen>Student</fen>.
The time when the student is studying.

The <fen>Place</fen> is the location within which the studying takes place.

NOTE: Consider whether a possible <fen>Place</fen> phrase is really where the training took place or is rather part of a description of the <fen>Institution</fen>.
A stable bounded area.  It is typically the designation of the nouns of Locale-derived frames.
The activity that is carried out in the <fen>Locale</fen>.
